<section class="section-parchment section-pad">
  <div class="page-container" style="max-width: 64rem;">
    <div class="grid-2col" style="gap: 3rem; align-items: start;">
      <div class="prose-ki" style="max-width: none;">
        <p class="overline">Role</p>
        <h2>The tooling follows the model.</h2>
        <p>The harness is the canonical source for the reusable tooling. It generalises patterns proven in Arcadia Principal; it does not define the Knowledge Islands philosophy or model.</p>
        <p>This website publishes an accessible orientation to the harness. The harness repository remains canonical for its documentation, releases, and executable artifacts.</p>
        <p><a href="https://github.com/knowledgeislands/ki-agentic-harness">Explore the harness repository</a></p>
      </div>
      <div style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: 2rem; box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgb(26 32 48 / 6%);">
        <p class="overline">Installation</p>
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Start from the right place</h2>
        <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">Install the harness once for your user environment, then bootstrap each repository you want to govern. The two stable Knowledge Islands URLs remain the public contract while the harness owns the executable scripts.</p>
        <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.25rem;">
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Install for your user</h3>
            <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Adds the user-level harness payload. Run once before governing repositories.</p>
            <pre style="overflow-x: auto; padding: 1rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); background: var(--color-navy); color: var(--color-parchment); font-size: 0.8125rem;"><code>curl -fsSL https://knowledgeislands.info/harness/install | sh</code></pre>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.0625rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">Bootstrap a repository</h3>
            <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Run from the repository you want to govern. It creates that repository's governance machinery without changing the rest of your user environment.</p>
            <pre style="overflow-x: auto; padding: 1rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md); background: var(--color-navy); color: var(--color-parchment); font-size: 0.8125rem;"><code>curl -fsSL https://knowledgeislands.info/harness/bootstrap | sh</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.875rem; margin: 1rem 0 0;">Both commands follow the redirect with <code>-L</code>. Supply any script arguments, including a supported pinned ref, after <code>sh -s --</code>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
